 on new morning it was a bright sunshiny day the frost 
 had been so strong and was still so strong that the fallen snow 
 had become a hard mass and one could walk upon it the bells of the little town were tolling for church student holberg wrapped himself up in his woollen cloak and wanted to go to the town 
 
 over the the crows and daws were flying with loud 
 cries one could hardly hear the church bells for their screaming 
 mother soren stood in front of the house filling a brass pot with 
