 he was invited to take a mug of brown beer with treacle and sugar 
 the discourse fell upon mother soren but the tax collector did not know much about her and indeed few knew much about her she did not belong to the island of falster he said she had a little property of her own at one time her husband was a common sailor a fellow of a very hot temper and had killed a sailor of dragor and he beat his wife and yet she defended him 
 
