 and all that has been written 
 what rascal was it who said that man was a featherless biped and then i met a pretty girl of my acquaintance who is as beautiful as the spring worthy to be called floreal and who is delighted enraptured as happy as the angels because a wretch yesterday a frightful banker all spotted with deigned to take a fancy to her alas woman keeps on the watch for a protector as much as for a lover cats chase mice as well as birds 
 two months ago that young woman was virtuous in an attic she adjusted little brass rings in the of corsets what do you call it 
